title: What is the difference between [4,5], [4,5), (4,5], and (4,5)? - Quora

response.answer_text: [ ] these represents closed bracket which means that a no. Is included . And ( ) the represents the no. aren't included. [4,5] this means that 4 and 5 are included. [4,5) this means that 4 is included whereas 5 isn't. (4,5] this means that 5 in included and 4 isnt. (4,5) this means that both 4 and 5 aren't included.

Square bracket [] means inclusion of that limit where as () bracket refers to exclusion of that limit. For example- [4,5) means any value lying between 4 and 5 including 4 4≤ x ≤ 5 [4,5) means 4≤ x < 5 (4,5] means 4< x ≤ 5 (4,5) means 4< x < 5 I hope it helps. :)
